sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J34000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Half Adder (HA), 2x PoPS input, 2x PoPS output
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part will model a half adder, i.e., a gene circuit with two inputs and two outputs. The half adder system can add the two input signals, interpreted as binary values. The output signals give the sum of the discretized input signals.
I1 I2 O1 O2 0 0 0 0 0 1 0 1 1 0 0 1 1 1 1 0
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ETH Zurich 2006 iGEM team
